<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Deliberately empty. Tusk ships outside the App Store, so it is not sandboxed:
network access, file access, and spawning the Claude Code PTY all work with no
entitlement. The hardened runtime is applied by codesign at signing time and is
not an entitlement.

Notably absent: com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation. It is not
needed (the vendored dylibs carry the same Developer ID as the app, so library
validation passes) and adding it would let any library be injected into Tusk.

Add an entitlement only when a concrete failure proves it necessary. See
docs/RELEASING.md. Note: XML comments may not contain a double hyphen, which is
easy to trip over when writing codesign flags in here. The entitlements parser
rejects the whole file if you do.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
</dict>
</plist>
